d even murders, and argues that violence resulted primarily from workplace conditions including on-the-job exploitation, racial tension, bureaucratization, and hypermasculinity. This explosive book reveals that workplace violence has been a constant aspect of class conflict – and that our understanding needs to go deeper.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAutomobile industry and tradexHistoryx20th centuryxCanada. 0aAutomobile industry and tradexHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aAutomobile industry and tradezCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aAutomobile industry and tradezUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aAutomobile industry workerszCanadaxSocial conditionsy20th century. 0aAutomobile industry workerszUnited StatesxSocial conditionsy20th century. 0aViolence in the workplacexHistoryx20th centuryxCanada. 0aViolence in the workplacexHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aViolence in the workplacexSocial aspectszCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aViolence in the workplacexSocial aspectszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aViolencexSocial aspectszCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aViolencexSocial aspectszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311127365508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017z978311127619908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311141793640uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077483455140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774834551423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774834551/original  a978-3-11-127365-5  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-127619-9  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017